For Typescript Installation:

Install node js
Install typescript
	 npm i -g typescript  // npm install -g typescript 

for porject creation you have to write below command 	npm init -y  tsc --init
npm init -y will create nodejs project with default settings and create package.json file
tsc --init will initialize typescript in this project and create tsconfig.json file
vs code install
how to open vs code in particular directory
code .	

Difference between let, const and var:

1. let:
  a. The scope of a let variable is block scope.
  b. It can be updated but cannot be re-declared in the same scope.
  c. It can be declared without initialization.

2. const:
  a.The scope of a const variable is block scope.
  b.It can neither be updated or re-declared in any scope.
  c.It cannot be declared without initialization.

3. var:
  a.The scope of a var variable is functional or global scope.	
  b.It can be updated and re-declared in the same scope.	
  c.It can be declared without initialization.	
